genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica mexiquense
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica mexiquense is a traditional music genre that originated in the state of Mexico. It is characterized by the use of brass instruments and percussion, with lyrics that often depict the history and culture of the state. The music is lively and energetic, with a strong emphasis on dance and celebration. Musica mexiquense is an important part of the cultural heritage of the state, and is often performed at festivals and other cultural events.
